# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# GLOBAL IGNORE RULES FOR A MONOREPO-LIKE MERN PROJECT
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Dependency Folders
# Ignore all node_modules folders in subdirectories.
# This prevents checking in project dependencies.
*/node_modules

# 2. Environment Variables
# These files contain sensitive information (like MONGO_URI and JWT_SECRET).
# Never commit them!
.env
.env.local

# 3. Backend Build and Runtime Files (Node/Express)
# These are files generated by the backend
# Example: If you bundle or use logs
/dashboard-backend/dist
/dashboard-backend/logs

# 4. Frontend Build and Caching (React/Vite)
# Ignore the production build output and cache directories specific to Vite/React
/dashboard-frontend/dist
/dashboard-frontend/build
/dashboard-frontend/.vite
/dashboard-frontend/coverage

# 5. OS and Editor Files
# Ignore common operating system and IDE/Editor generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*